<h2>
    Understanding Winter Steelhead
</h2>
<p>
    Steelhead are a type of sea-run rainbow trout that return to freshwater rivers to spawn. Winter steelhead differ from summer steelhead primarily in timing and behavior.
</p>
<h3>
    Key Traits of Winter Steelhead:
</h3>
<ul>
    <li>
        <strong>Larger and Stronger</strong>: Due to time in the ocean, they return bulkier and battle-ready.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Aggressive Fighters</strong>: Expect intense runs and aerial acrobatics.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Migration Timing</strong>: Most arrive between <strong>December and March</strong>, with peak runs in <strong>January and February</strong>.
    </li>
</ul>
<p>
    Knowing how these fish behave in cold, high-water conditions will dramatically increase your odds.
</p>
