<h2>
    Ideal Fishing Techniques for Winter Steelhead
</h2>
<p>
    Winter steelhead won’t bite just anything—you need to present your offerings with skill. Here are top methods:
</p>
<h3>
    Drift Fishing
</h3>
<p>
    A classic technique where you bounce bait or lures along the bottom using split shot. Use <strong>roe, sand shrimp</strong>, or <strong>soft beads</strong>for success.
</p>
<h3>
    Bobber and Jig
</h3>
<p>
    This method shines in <strong>slower water or deep slots</strong>. Bright pink or orange jigs are particularly effective in cloudy conditions.
</p>
<h3>
    Fly Fishing
</h3>
<p>
    Swinging flies like <strong>Egg-sucking Leeches</strong> or <strong>Intruders</strong> can entice aggressive strikes. Use <strong>sink tips</strong> to reach deep-holding fish.
</p>
